# Strip comments from Rust sources in the committed/pushed copy via the
# `stripcomments` clean filter. The working tree keeps its comments; only the
# blob stored in git (and therefore what lands on GitHub) is comment-free.
#
# The filter command lives in the local repo config (it is NOT committed), so
# each clone must enable it once:  tools/setup-git-filters.sh   (or .ps1)
# Without it configured, git falls back to identity (comments pass through).
*.rs filter=stripcomments
